title: Pistons announce injuries to Blake, Jackson and Baynes
text:
Pistons announce injuries to Blake (concussion), Jackson (thigh) and Baynes (ankle) THE ASSOCIATED PRESS   8:47   8:48   
People: 
Men's sports (2326) 

AUBURN HILLS, Michigan — Detroit Pistons guard Steve Blake is recovering from a concussion, guard Reggie Jackson has a bruised thigh and center Aaron Baynes has a sore right ankle. 
The team announced the injuries Friday. 
Blake's concussion occurred Wednesday in practice. The Pistons say he will go through the NBA's mandatory return-to-participation protocol until he is deemed free of symptoms. There is no timetable for his return.
